Key Match Events: Game 5 of the American League Division Series was moved up due to rainy weather
Cleveland Guardians forced the game with a 5-4 victory
Pre-Game Insights: The game was moved from 8:08 p.m. ET to 1:08 p.m. ET due to rain
Weather conditions were a factor in the scheduling change
Post-Match Reflections: The Cleveland Guardians secured a spot in the American League Championship Series with the win
The Detroit Tigers faced elimination with the loss
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was originally scheduled for Saturday evening but was moved to the afternoon
The series winner would face the New York Yankees in the ALCS
